```

In Python, inheritance is implemented using the `__` keyword. A class can have one or more attributes and methods that are declared as "abstract" by defining them with the keyword `abstract`. This means that they can be defined in an abstract class, but cannot be defined in a concrete class derived from the abstract class. An instance of the derived class will inherit all the attributes and methods of the abstract class.

